Average Post Hiatus (Part 1) [Facebook SQL Interview Question]

Question:-
Given a table of Facebook posts, for each user who posted at least twice in 2021,
write a query to find the number of days between each userâ€™s first post of the year and 
last post of the year in the year 2021. Output the user and number of the days between each 
user's first and last post.

Code:-

SELECT user_id,MAX(post_date::date) - MIN(post_date::date) AS days_between
FROM posts
WHERE DATE_PART('YEAR',post_date) = '2021'
GROUP BY user_id
HAVING COUNT(post_id) > 1;
